				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: double attack, offhand bug<a name="53064"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 2:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I see no mention of correcting the beastlord or the bard issues with double attack in the off-hand on test.  What is mentioned is a correction to some worn effects which increase double attack.
<br />

<br />
The list of changes can be found at http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=testing&amp;message.id=2568
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">
<br />
- The Ferocity line of spells will now increase your chance of double attack for classes without innate double attack.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
They mean the worn effects Ferocity I, Ferocity II, and Ferocity III on GoD equipment will work with bards and beastlords now.  (Most of these are found on good bard items!)
<br />

<br />
Some members of the Concert Hall incorrectly posted that this was a beastlord spell fix.  While there are beastlord spells with Ferocity in their names (namely Ferocity and Sha's Ferocity), these do not increase the chance of double attack, so would not be the ones they are refering to.
<br />

<br />
Some unpublished parses showed that Ferocity was working already with bards, despite the developers claims that it did not.  Hopefully this fix will not have an adverse effect for those who believed it was already working.
<br />

<br />
This change does not effect the vast majority of bards.  Very few items are involved, and only one item is from pre-KT GoD.  In fact, I know of only one item that is pre-Qvic.
<br />

<br />
- Lall
<br />
Bold Bardess with 113 Melodic Tools
<br />
Shards of Avalon, Xegony.</span></td>
